# Agent Planning Workflow

Maintain project plans and create well-structured Linear issues.

## Maintaining MASTER_PLAN.md

`docs/plans/MASTER_PLAN.md` is the living priority document. Update it when:
- Phases complete (move to Completed, FIFO)
- Priorities shift (reorder Current Focus)
- New work is approved (move from Backlog to Upcoming)

Keep it under 100 lines. Link to sub-plans and specs, never duplicate their content.

## Creating Linear Issues from Specs

When a spec in `docs/specs/` or a phase plan in `docs/plans/PHASE_*.md` is approved:

1. Break the spec into implementable issues (1-4 hours of work each)
2. For each issue, call `save_issue` with:
   - `team`: "FrenchForest"
   - `state`: "Needs Approval"
   - `labels`: ["Needs Approval", "PersonalAgent"]
   - `project`: The relevant Linear project
   - `description`: Use the issue template below

## Issue Description Template

```markdown
## Spec
- `docs/specs/SPEC_NAME.md` (section X.Y)

## ADRs
- ADR-XXXX (relevant decision)

## Files
- `src/personal_agent/...`
- `tests/...`

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Criterion 1
- [ ] Criterion 2
- [ ] Tests pass
- [ ] No new lint errors
```

## Planning Constraints

- Every issue must link to a spec or ADR
- Issues should be small enough to implement in one session
- For issues touching >2 files, include a brief implementation approach
- Never create issues without `state: "Needs Approval"`
- Group related issues under a Linear project
